description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Would you like to work for a progressive organisation where staff have a voice? If so join Sirona care &amp; health where you will be part of a team which is supportive and caring and where your development is important to us.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be based in Weston and Worle or Langford, North Somerset providing holistic community nursing care to patients within their own homes and clinics. Providing care over a 7 day period, you will have access to a comprehensive training package which will enable you to meet the ever increasing challenges of complex care in the community.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You would be undertaking nursing roles such as administration of medication, pressure ulcer prevention and management, wound care, catheterisation and End of life care. Being part of the multidisciplinary team is a key part of your role.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;span&gt;The team works closely with each other and with other key partners in order to provide the best possible care and treatment to our patients and their carers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information on this exciting opportunity please contact Di Paling on 07990554089 or Jo Keen on 07887764486&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
